AUTOMATIC QC

1. General 

 - duplicated dates, comas, -999, -888 


2. Extreme value check
 
 - Fixed ranges: 
 - Tmax >= 60 | Tmax =< -10 
 - Tmin >= 40 | Tmin =< -30
 - limits: Q25 - 4*IRQ < Temp | Q75 + IRQ*4 > Temp


3. Internal consistency check

 - Consistency among variables
 - Tmax <= Tmin
 - Tmax = Tmin = 0


4. Temporal coherence check

 - Consecutive repetidos >8 days 
 - daily Jumps > 15°C


5. Spatial coherence check

 - Only done where area highly amount of stations (jungle may is not posible)
 - Estacion candiata vs estaciones vecinas (al menos 4 estaciones)
 - Debido a la información faltante, se realizo una imputación antes de convertirles a valores de   percentiles, el procedimiento dado por https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/norm/norm.pdf
 - Values to percentil, higher differences between the same day (78 o -78th) 
 - Cita http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/joc.1850/abstract


ENHANCED AND VISUAL QC

6. Precision inconsistencies 

 - count the amount of decimales grouped (.0, .1, .. ., .9) by year
 - years with more than 40% of data in any level is deleted
 - years with more than 35% and 0% of data in at least three levels (anyone) at the same year is deleted
 - years with less than 35% of data is deleted (need to define)


